Interface Individual.Disjoint<O,J,D extends Individual<O,J>>

  • Type Parameters:
    O - the ontology.
    J - the type of Ground and EntitySet managed by this Descriptor.
    D - the type of the Individual descriptors instantiated during buildDisjointIndividual() through getNewDisjointIndividual(Object, Object).
    All Superinterfaces:
    Axiom, Axiom.Descriptor<O,J>, Individual<O,J>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IndividualExpression.Disjoint<D>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefinitionIndividualDesc, FullIndividualDesc
    Enclosing interface:
    Individual<O,J>

    public static interface Individual.Disjoint<O,J,D extends Individual<O,J>>
extends Individual<O,J>
    Implementation of this interface enables a Individual to have the Individual.Disjoint expression.

      • readExpressionAxioms

        default java.util.List<Axiom.MappingIntent> readExpressionAxioms()
        Description copied from interface: Axiom.Descriptor
        This method is used to update specific Axiom.EntitySet (or Axiom.ExpressionEntitySet) by synchronizing the internal state of the descriptor with the queried OWL structure, such that they are equal. It is based on EntitySet#synchroniseFrom(EntitySet).
        Specified by:
        readExpressionAxioms in interface Axiom.Descriptor<O,J>
        Returns:
        the changes made in the Axiom.EntitySet during the reading. Note that the elements of the returned list, may not have the Axiom.MappingIntent.getOntologyChanges() field initialised (i.e.: Void).

      • buildDisjointIndividual

        default java.util.Set<D> buildDisjointIndividual()
        Create an Axiom.Descriptor set where each element represents the different individuals from this description. Each of Individuals are instantiated through the method getNewDisjointIndividual(Object, Object); this is called for all getDisjointIndividuals().
        Returns:
        the set of Individuals that describes the entities that are different from this described ontological individualDescriptor.

      • getNewDisjointIndividual

        D getNewDisjointIndividual(J instance,
                           O ontology)
        This method is called by buildDisjointIndividual() and its purpose is to instantiate a new Individual to represent an equivalent individualDescriptor from this Individual Descriptor.
        Parameters:
        instance - the instance to ground the new Individual.
        ontology - the ontology in which ground the new Individual.
        Returns:
        a new Axiom.Descriptor for all the individuals that are equivalent from the one described by this interface.

      • synchroniseDisjointIndividualToExpressionAxioms

        default Axiom.EntitySet.SynchronisationIntent<J> synchroniseDisjointIndividualToExpressionAxioms()
        It calls EntitySet#synchroniseTo(EntitySet) with queryDisjointIndividuals() as input parameter. This computes the changes to be performed in the OWL representation for synchronise it with respect to getDisjointIndividuals(). This should be done by Axiom.Descriptor.writeExpressionAxioms().
        Returns:
        the changes to be done to synchronise this structure with the different individuals from Axiom.Descriptor.getInstance(); to the OWL representation.

      • synchroniseDisjointIndividualFromExpressionAxioms

        default Axiom.EntitySet.SynchronisationIntent<J> synchroniseDisjointIndividualFromExpressionAxioms()
        It calls EntitySet#synchroniseFrom(EntitySet) with queryDisjointIndividuals() as input parameter. This computes the changes to be performed into the getDisjointIndividuals() in order to synchronise it with respect to an OWL representation. This is be done by readExpressionAxioms().
        Returns:
        the changes to be done to synchronise the different individuals from Axiom.Descriptor.getInstance(); from an OWL representation to this Descriptor.
